verbose_text: In contrast to the observed maximum acetylation of mitochondrial proteins during the night under fasting conditions because of the more active SIRT3 activity during this period, we observed, under our night feeding conditions, maximal acetylation of these proteins during the day, mostly as a consequence of the food dependent increase in acetyl-CoA synthesis.
evidence: acetylation of mitochondrial proteins during the night under fasting conditions because of the more active SIRT3
